==English==
===Noun===
'''cousin''' (''plural'' '''[[cousins]]''')

# [[son]] or [[daughter]] of someone's [[uncle]] or [[aunt]]
# relation who is not a direct ancestor or descendant, more distantly related than an aunt, uncle, niece, nephew, etc.  Relations who have a common grandparent are called ''[[first cousin]]s'', those who have a common [[great-grandparent]] are called ''[[second cousin]]s'', a [[great-great-grandparent]] ''[[third cousin]]s'', and so forth.

====Usage Note====
If two cousins are one generation apart, they are called '''[[once removed]]'''; if two generations apart, '''[[twice removed]]''', etc.  For example, if Phil and Marie are first cousins, and Marie has a son Andre, Phil and Andre are [[first cousins once removed]].

